 in both the conventional and quantum spin Hall phases, much greater\nthan the thermal energy kT = 25 meV at room temperature, suggest that ultrathin\nNa3Bi is suitable for room temperature topological transistor operation.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 22 May 2018 03:44:24 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 5 Feb 2019 03:37:20 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-02-06"}
